{
  "texts": [
    "did not propose a taxonomy for techniques used in social network anonymization.",
    "Nevertheless, we have derived a classification scheme based on the studies they reviewed, which is graphically illustrated in Fig. 6.In 2019, Sathiya Devi et al.",
    "conducted a literature survey concerning anonymization methods in social networks [142].",
    "Their primary focus was on techniques used to maintain the attribute privacy of social network users.",
    "In line with this, they grouped these methods into five distinct categories: K-anonymity, L-diversity, T-closeness, Slicing, and Differential Privacy."
  ]
}